{
  "texts": [
    "Dictionaries as Adult Tools: Dictionaries, being compiled by adult lexicographers, reflect an adult's understanding of language.",
    "They are designed to provide definitions and explanations for users who already have a foundational understanding of the language, rather than to teach language from the ground up.",
    "The MinSets identified in dictionaries, while indicative of a core vocabulary that can define other words, should not be directly equated with the foundational vocabulary necessary for language acquisition in children.",
    "The process of language learning, especially for children, involves more than just learning a set of core words.",
    "It includes contextual understanding, social interaction, and crucially, sensorimotor experiences that help ground language in the physical world."
  ]
}